      "author": "Feng6611",
      "description": "## File Ignore 1.1.0\n\nThis release focuses on **safety, predictability, and recovery**.\n\n### Highlights\n- **Plan before execute**: Hide/Show now computes a rename plan before running.\n- **Safer batch execution**: automatically skips protected paths, target conflicts, duplicate targets, and nested child entries when the parent directory is already being renamed.\n- **Recovery support**: the latest batch state is persisted so interrupted runs can be undone from the settings page.\n- **Clearer product messaging**: docs now explicitly state that File Ignore works by renaming files/folders on disk.\n\n### Included improvements\n- rename preview in the confirmation flow\n- recovery / undo entry in settings\n- centralized shared settings/types\n- version metadata aligned to `1.1.0`\n- updated README and Chinese README\n\n### Validation\n- `npm run build`\n- post-commit review\n",
